clue: This fabric used in coats usually comes from the Bactrian type

response: camel hair

clue: Fabric made from this tall grass is all the rage in part due to its antibacterial properties

response: bamboo

clue: This lace named for a town in France was paired in song with "a pretty face and a ponytail hanging down"

response: Chantilly lace

clue: This woven fabric used for suits sounds like a poetic contraction referencing the future

response: twill

clue: Sails & beach umbrellas are 2 items traditionally made of this hempen or flaxen cloth

response: canvas

